<paragraph blockId="158.[1369,2573,2858,3167]" pageId="158" pageNumber="761">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1369,1524,2858,2892]" pageId="158" pageNumber="761">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Thomas, 1906" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[1544,2023,2858,2892]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Dasymys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="158" pageNumber="761" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">Dasymys montanus Thomas, 1906</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3864424906" pageId="158" pageNumber="761">“[Mount] Ruwenzori East, Uganda, 12,500&quot; [= 3810 m],” Uganda</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="158" pageNumber="761" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="158.[1369,2573,2858,3167]" pageId="158" pageNumber="761">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[1369,1614,2941,2970]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Dasymys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="158" pageNumber="761" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="montanus">Dasymys montanus</taxonomicName>
was previously considered to be part of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Sundevall" baseAuthorityYear="1847" box="[2175,2330,2941,2970]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Dasymys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="158" pageNumber="761" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="incomtus">D. incomtus</taxonomicName>
, but was elevated to species rank on basis of morphological data. It is distinctive in having very short and uniformly dark tail, small body, and small skull size. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[1369,2254,3054,3088]" pageId="158" pageNumber="761" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6887854" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6887854" box="[1369,2254,3054,3088]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6887854/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="158" pageNumber="761" startId="158.[1369,1541,3054,3088]" targetBox="[165,757,306,720]" targetPageId="159">
<paragraph blockId="158.[1369,2573,2858,3167]" box="[1369,2254,3054,3088]" pageId="158" pageNumber="761">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1369,1545,3054,3088]" pageId="158" pageNumber="761">Distribution.</emphasis>
Rwenzori Mts, Uganda, at altitudes above 2600 m.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="159" lastPageNumber="762" pageId="158" pageNumber="761" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="158.[1369,2573,2858,3167]" pageId="158" pageNumber="761">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1369,1617,3094,3128]" pageId="158" pageNumber="761">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 132-156 mm, tail 93-115 mm, ear 17-19 mm, hindfoot 28-31 mm; weight 69-100 g. As with all 
<taxonomicName box="[1922,2032,3138,3167]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Dasymys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL,GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="158" pageNumber="761" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Dasymys</taxonomicName>
, fur of the Rwenzori Shaggy Rat is soft,
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6887892" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6887892" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6887892/files/figure.png" pageId="158" pageNumber="761" startId="158.[95,125,3260,3285]" targetBox="[12,2727,14,3649]" targetPageId="157">
