<subSubSection box="[781,1348,614,643]" pageId="159" pageNumber="762" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="159.[781,1375,303,723]" box="[781,1348,614,643]" pageId="159" pageNumber="762">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[781,891,614,643]" pageId="159" pageNumber="762">Habitat.</emphasis>
Alpine and subalpine meadows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="159" pageNumber="762" type="food_feeding">
<paragraph blockId="159.[781,1375,303,723]" pageId="159" pageNumber="762">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[781,1048,650,684]" pageId="159" pageNumber="762">Food and Feeding.</emphasis>
The Rwenzori Shaggy Rat is presumably herbivorous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
